                'tag' => NULL,
                'short_intro' => 'The Dell Latitude 7440 is a business Ultrabook that packs a lot of technology into its durable 3.9-pound frame. Starting at $999, our $1,849 14-inch Dell Latitude 7440 sports a fourth-generation Core i5-4300U processor, a full HD 1080p touch-screen display and a 256GB SSD for speedy performance. But is Dell\'s new Latitude the best business notebook you can get?',
                'full_intro' => '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head></head><body><h3><strong>Design</strong></h3><p>The Latitude 7440 sports a sleek and attractive all-black design. The notebook\'s lid is made of a sturdy soft-touch carbon fiber material that reminds us of the Kevlar back on Motorola Droid phones. This carbon fiber is backed by an aluminum frame and reinforced steel hinges.</p><h3><strong>Ports</strong></h3><p><img src="../../../upload/image/product/e7440/1555641575dell-latitude-e7440-port.jpg" alt="" /><img style="height: 61px; width: 437px;" src="../../../upload/images/product/e7440/1555641575dell-latitude-e7440-port.jpg" alt="" /></p><p>Built for productivity, the Dell Latitude 7440 comes with all the ports you need. The laptop\'s right side houses an audio and microphone combination jack, a USB 3.0 port and a lock slot. The left side features a SmartCard reader and an SD Card slot. On the notebook\'s rear, you\'ll find a power jack, HDMI, two more USB 3.0 slots, a mini DisplayPort and Ethernet. Dell has also included a docking connector on the bottom of the notebook.</p></body></html>',
