                'full_intro' => '<!DOCTYPE html><html><head></head><body><p><span style="color: #494949; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;">The easiest ways to differentiate each Galaxy Tab E model is by their display sizes and Android- operating system version. The original 9.6-inch Galaxy Tab E was released back in 2014, running Android 5.1. This larger version is powered by a quad-core 1.2GHz Qualcomm Snapdragon 410 CPU and comes with 1.5GB of RAM and 16GB of storage. A microSD card slot allows you to expand to up to 128GB of storage space.</span></p></body></html>',
